==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|drĭlʹ jĭg'}}

===Noun===

{{en-noun}}

# A type of [[jig]] that expedites repetitive hole center location on multiple interchangeable parts by acting as a template to guide the [[twist drill]] into the precise location of each intended hole center.

===Historical note===
Since the widespread penetration of the manufacturing industry by CNC machine tools, in which the servocontrols are capable of moving the tool to the correct location automatically, the need for drill jigs (and for the jobs of the manual-drill-press operators who used them) is a fraction of what it previously was.

